## Changelog

### 1.7.0 (2026-03-25)
- Token optimization: prompt-architect and code-reviewer downgraded from opus to sonnet
- Token optimization: git-manager downgraded to haiku for simple git operations
- Trimmed verbose templates from product-manager, business-analyst, database-expert (agents generate templates on their own)
- Memory size guideline added to all 15 agents — keep memory concise, summarize insights

### 1.6.0 (2026-03-25)
- QA monitoring options in /init-project: post-commit hook, scheduled scan, both, or manual only
- Users choose their preferred monitoring level during project setup

### 1.5.0 (2026-03-23)
- Full documentation sync: README and Confluence guide updated with all features
- Added: cross-agent issue resolution, handoff protocol, accessibility menu, deployment platforms, communication rules, /update-agents

### 1.4.2 (2026-03-23)
- /update-agents command: one-command agent update with auto-recovery on failures

### 1.4.1 (2026-03-23)
- qa-expert flags missing accessibility menu as high severity finding in audits
- Triggers @ISSUE → ui-designer automatically to create it

### 1.4.0 (2026-03-23)
- Accessibility menu is now a mandatory part of every web project
- ui-designer auto-creates floating accessibility widget (font size, contrast, grayscale, readable font, animations, cursor, reading guide)
- frontend-developer verifies accessibility menu is integrated, flags ui-designer if missing

### 1.3.0 (2026-03-23)
- Cross-Agent Issue Resolution: agents flag problems outside their domain, orchestrator auto-routes to the right agent, fixes happen automatically
- Resolution chains: if fixing agent finds another issue, it chains to the next agent (max depth 3)
- User informed after the fact, not asked to intervene

### 1.2.0 (2026-03-23)
- "Speak plainly" rule added to CLAUDE.md — all agents use simple everyday language with users
- Planning agents avoid jargon: "login system" instead of "Auth", "first basic version" instead of "MVP"
- Technical terms reserved for code and agent-to-agent handoffs only

### 1.1.0 (2026-03-23)
- Interactive clarification: prompt-architect asks guiding questions before refining
- Interactive discovery: business-analyst presents options at key decision points
- Interactive product definition: product-manager works through scope, priority, UX, and trade-offs with the user
- Interactive architecture: architect presents approach options with trade-offs before designing
- /check-updates command and auto-update notifications

### 1.0.0 (2026-03-23)
- 15 specialized agents (prompt-architect, business-analyst, product-manager, architect, frontend-developer, ui-designer, backend-developer, database-expert, devops-engineer, code-reviewer, security-analyst, performance-optimizer, qa-expert, tech-writer, git-manager)
- 6 slash commands (/init-project, /full-audit, /new-feature, /fix-bug, /security-check, /document)
- Safety hooks (PreToolUse) blocking destructive operations
- Micro-Checkpoint Protocol (PROCEED confirmation)
- Agent Handoff Protocol for pipeline continuity
- Smart routing in /new-feature (skips irrelevant agents)
- Dynamic tech stack detection (agents read CLAUDE.md, not hardcoded)
- Persistent memory system per agent
- Audit report system (.claude/audits/)
- Deployment platform knowledge (Supabase, Vercel, Railway, Fly.io, etc.)
- "Do, don't instruct" rule — agents execute, users supervise
